The paper deals with the problem of PAC-learning graphical models, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of submodular optimization problems is a common technique in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and information theory (cs.IT). The problem of treewidth is also related to computational complexity (cs.CC).
